Subject: http://purl.org/iot/vocab/m3-lite#AirTemperature
Object: Air Temperature, Weather Temperature, Ambient Temperature
ObjectTerm: Air Temperature, Weather Temperature, Ambient Temperature

Subject: http://www.onem2m.org/ontology/Base_Ontology/base_ontology#ThingProperty
Object:
A Value (Class: Value) denotes a property of a Thing. A Value can e.g. be observed or influenced by devices, or it constitutes static data about a Thing.
E.g. the indoor temperature of the room could be a Value of a Thing "room".
A Value of a thing can concern a certain Aspect, e.g. the indoor temperature concerns the Aspect "Temperature" that could be measured by a temperature sensor.
A Value of a Thing can have meta data
ObjectTerm:
A Value (Class: Value) denotes a property of a Thing. A Value can e.g. be observed or influenced by devices, or it constitutes static data about a Thing.
E.g. the indoor temperature of the room could be a Value of a Thing "room".
A Value of a thing can concern a certain Aspect, e.g. the indoor temperature concerns the Aspect "Temperature" that could be measured by a temperature sensor.
A Value of a Thing can have meta data

Subject: http://purl.org/iot/vocab/m3-lite#AirTemperature
Object: The temperature of the air that would be indicated by a thermometer exposed to the air at a location sheltered from direct solar radiation.
ObjectTerm: The temperature of the air that would be indicated by a thermometer exposed to the air at a location sheltered from direct solar radiation.

Subject: http://www.onem2m.org/ontology/Base_Ontology/base_ontology#Thing
Object:
A Thing in oneM2M  (Class: Thing) is an entity that can be identified in the oneM2M System. 
A Thing that is not a Device is not able to conmmunicate electronically with its environment. However, the sub-class of Thing that is able to interact electronically is called a "Device".
A Thing may have ThingProperties (Object Property: hasThingProperty). A Thing can have relations to other things (Object Property: hasThingRelation).
Since a Thing that is not a Device is not able to conmmunicate electronically it cannot influence the value of its ThingProperties or being influenced by it. Similarly a Thing cannot document its - real-world - relationships (via hasThingRelation) to other Things.

E.g. A room that is modelled in oneM2M would be a Thing that could have a room-temperature as a ThingProperty and could have a relationship "isAdjacentTo" to another room
ObjectTerm:
A Thing in oneM2M  (Class: Thing) is an entity that can be identified in the oneM2M System. 
A Thing that is not a Device is not able to conmmunicate electronically with its environment. However, the sub-class of Thing that is able to interact electronically is called a "Device".
A Thing may have ThingProperties (Object Property: hasThingProperty). A Thing can have relations to other things (Object Property: hasThingRelation).
Since a Thing that is not a Device is not able to conmmunicate electronically it cannot influence the value of its ThingProperties or being influenced by it. Similarly a Thing cannot document its - real-world - relationships (via hasThingRelation) to other Things.

E.g. A room that is modelled in oneM2M would be a Thing that could have a room-temperature as a ThingProperty and could have a relationship "isAdjacentTo" to another room

Subject: http://purl.org/iot/vocab/m3-lite#WaterTemperature
Object: Sea surface temperature (SST) is the water temperature close to the ocean's surface.
ObjectTerm: Sea surface temperature (SST) is the water temperature close to the ocean's surface.

Subject: http://purl.org/iot/vocab/m3-lite#FoodTemperature
Object: Measure of temperature of the food.
ObjectTerm: Measure of temperature of the food.

Subject: http://purl.org/iot/vocab/m3-lite#VoltageSensor
Object: A device designed to respond to physical stimuli such as temperature, light, magnetism, or movement, and to transmit resulting impulses for interpretation.
ObjectTerm: A device designed to respond to physical stimuli such as temperature, light, magnetism, or movement, and to transmit resulting impulses for interpretation.

Subject: http://purl.org/iot/vocab/m3-lite#DewPointTemperature
Object: The temperature at which dew forms and is a measure of atmospheric moisture. It is the temperature to which air must be cooled at constant pressure and water content to reach saturation. A higher dew point indicates more moisture in the air; a dew point greater than 20 Degree C (68 Degree F) is considered uncomfortable and greater than 22 Degree C (72 Degree F) is considered to be extremely humid.
ObjectTerm: The temperature at which dew forms and is a measure of atmospheric moisture. It is the temperature to which air must be cooled at constant pressure and water content to reach saturation. A higher dew point indicates more moisture in the air; a dew point greater than 20 Degree C (68 Degree F) is considered uncomfortable and greater than 22 Degree C (72 Degree F) is considered to be extremely humid.

Subject: http://purl.oclc.org/NET/UNIS/fiware/iot-lite#Attribute
Object: An attribute of an IoT object that can be exposed by an IoT service (i.e. a room (IoT Object) has a temperature (Attribute), that can be exposed by a temperature sensor (IoT device).
ObjectTerm: An attribute of an IoT object that can be exposed by an IoT service (i.e. a room (IoT Object) has a temperature (Attribute), that can be exposed by a temperature sensor (IoT device).

Subject: http://purl.oclc.org/NET/UNIS/fiware/iot-lite#isAssociatedWith
Object: Defines the associations between objects and sensors (e.g. A table (object) has an attribute (temperature at the table) which is associated with a sensor (the temperature sensor of the room).
ObjectTerm: Defines the associations between objects and sensors (e.g. A table (object) has an attribute (temperature at the table) which is associated with a sensor (the temperature sensor of the room).

Subject: http://purl.org/iot/vocab/m3-lite#Kelvin
Object: Kelvin is a unit of measurement for temperature.
ObjectTerm: Kelvin is a unit of measurement for temperature.

Subject: http://www.onem2m.org/ontology/Base_Ontology/base_ontology#MetaData
Object:
MetaData (Class: MetaData) contain data (like units, precision-ranges …) about a Variable or about an Aspect. 
E.g. the indoor temperature could have meta data: "Degrees Celsius"
ObjectTerm:
MetaData (Class: MetaData) contain data (like units, precision-ranges …) about a Variable or about an Aspect. 
E.g. the indoor temperature could have meta data: "Degrees Celsius"

Subject: http://purl.oclc.org/NET/UNIS/fiware/iot-lite#hasUnit
Object: Links the sensor with the units of the quantity kind it measures (e.g. A sensor -sensor1- measures temperature in Celsius: senso1 hasUnit celsius).
ObjectTerm: Links the sensor with the units of the quantity kind it measures (e.g. A sensor -sensor1- measures temperature in Celsius: senso1 hasUnit celsius).

Subject: http://purl.org/iot/vocab/m3-lite#AirThermometer
Object: Device to measure the Air temperature of either indoor or outdoor atmosphere.
ObjectTerm: Device to measure the Air temperature of either indoor or outdoor atmosphere.

Subject: http://purl.org/iot/vocab/m3-lite#DewPoint
Object: It is the temperature to which air must be cooled at constant pressure to condense to form liquid.
ObjectTerm: It is the temperature to which air must be cooled at constant pressure to condense to form liquid.

Subject: http://purl.org/iot/vocab/m3-lite#BuildingTemperature
Object: Measure of building or room temperature.
ObjectTerm: Measure of building or room temperature.

Subject: http://purl.org/iot/vocab/m3-lite#RoadSurfaceThermometer
Object: Device used to measure the road Surface temperature.
ObjectTerm: Device used to measure the road Surface temperature.

Subject: http://purl.org/iot/vocab/m3-lite#BodyThermometer
Object: Device used to measure body temperature.
ObjectTerm: Device used to measure body temperature.

Subject: http://purl.org/iot/vocab/m3-lite#TemperatureWasteContainer
Object: The temperature of the air that would be indicated by a thermometer exposed to the air inside a waste container.
ObjectTerm: The temperature of the air that would be indicated by a thermometer exposed to the air inside a waste container.

Subject: http://purl.oclc.org/NET/UNIS/fiware/iot-lite#hasQuantityKind
Object: Links a sensor or an attribute with the quantity  kind it measures (e.g. A sensor -sensor1- measures temperature: sensor1 hasQuantityKind temperature).
ObjectTerm: Links a sensor or an attribute with the quantity  kind it measures (e.g. A sensor -sensor1- measures temperature: sensor1 hasQuantityKind temperature).

Subject: http://purl.org/iot/vocab/m3-lite#TemperatureEngine
Object: The temperature of a vehicle engine.
ObjectTerm: The temperature of a vehicle engine.

Subject: http://purl.org/iot/vocab/m3-lite#SoilTemperature
Object: Soil temperature is the bulk temperature of the soil, not the surface (skin) temperature.
ObjectTerm: Soil temperature is the bulk temperature of the soil, not the surface (skin) temperature.

Subject: http://purl.org/iot/vocab/m3-lite#DeltaDewPoint
Object: Difference between Dewpoint and surface temperatures.
ObjectTerm: Difference between Dewpoint and surface temperatures.

Subject: http://purl.org/iot/vocab/m3-lite#DegreeCelsius
Object: A temperature unit which is equal to one kelvin degree. However, they have their zeros at different points. The centigrade scale has its zero at 273.15 K.
ObjectTerm: A temperature unit which is equal to one kelvin degree. However, they have their zeros at different points. The centigrade scale has its zero at 273.15 K.

Subject: http://purl.org/iot/vocab/m3-lite#DegreeFahrenheit
Object: Measurement Unit to represent temperature on the Fahrenheit scale.
ObjectTerm: Measurement Unit to represent temperature on the Fahrenheit scale.

Subject: http://purl.org/iot/vocab/m3-lite#DeltaDewPointSensor
Object: Device that measures the difference between Dewpoint and surface temperatures.
ObjectTerm: Device that measures the difference between Dewpoint and surface temperatures.

Subject: http://purl.org/iot/vocab/m3-lite#BoardThermometer
Object: Device used to measure board temperature.
ObjectTerm: Device used to measure board temperature.

Subject: http://purl.oclc.org/NET/UNIS/fiware/iot-lite#Coverage
Object: The coverage of an IoT device (i.e. a temperature sensor inside a room has a coverage of that room).
ObjectTerm: The coverage of an IoT device (i.e. a temperature sensor inside a room has a coverage of that room).

Subject: http://purl.org/iot/vocab/m3-lite#Thermometer
Object: A device to measure the temperature in a room or outside.
ObjectTerm: A device to measure the temperature in a room or outside.
